Halve, peel and thinly slice the @red onion{1}(halved, peeled and thinly sliced). Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tbsp} in a #large saucepan{} over medium heat. Once hot, add the onion and season well with @salt{} and @black pepper{}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until the onion has softened and is starting to colour, ~{5-6%minutes}.

In the meantime, trim the @green beans{80%g}(trimmed). Pick the @mint{1}(leaves picked and roughly chopped) leaves from their stalks and roughly chop (discard the stalks). Peel the @orange{1}(peeled and sliced) and cut in half lengthways. Slice widthways into 1cm wide half-moons. Crumble the @feta cheese{100%g}(crumbled). Chop each @cooked beetroot{250%g}(chopped) into six segments.

Once the onion has caramelised, stir in the @ground cumin{2%tsp} and cook for ~{1%minute}. Pour the @water{240%ml} into the #pot{} and bring to the boil. Once boiling, stir in the @bulgur wheat{120%g}, bring back to the boil, pop a #lid{} on the pot and remove from the heat. Leave to the side for ~{12-15%minutes} or until ready to serve.

Meanwhile, fill another #large saucepan{} with water and bring to the boil. Once boiling, add the green beans and a pinch of @salt{}. Boil until just tender, ~{3-4%minutes}. Once cooked, drain in a #sieve{} and run under cold water to cool. Set to one side.

While the beans are cooking, pop the @honey{15%ml}, @wholegrain mustard{1%tsp} and @red wine vinegar{12%ml} into a #large salad bowl{}. Mix to combine then add the olive oil and season with salt and pepper to taste.

When everything is ready, fluff the bulgur wheat up with a #fork{} and stir in half the mint. Season with salt and pepper if necessary. Pop the beetroot, orange, green beans and @pea shoots{40%g} into the salad bowl and toss to coat in the dressing. Divide the bulgur between your bowls and pop the beetroot salad on top. Sprinkle over the crumbled feta and @flaked almonds{25%g}. Enjoy!

